<TITLE> Admin sees some shuffles </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 3 (bdnews24.com)The government made some shuffles in the administration on Monday, including an appointment on contract to the Planning Commission. Idris Ali, former member of the Planning Commission, who was on leave preparatory to retirement, was reappointed to the same position on a two-year contract. Mizanul Karim, a former additional chief engineer, was appointed to the directorate of education engineering for one year. Additional secretary Ranjit Kumar Biswas, who was earlier made Officer on Special Duty to the establishment ministry, was appointed chairman of Sugar and Food Industries Corporation on deputation. Bangladesh Civil Aviation Authority member on deputation Nayeem Hassan, a former group captain of the air force, was attached to the Armed Forces Division to be returned to the air force. bd
